---
title: rsh — REPL Sequence Diagram (v2, reflects actual code)
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Main
    participant Shell
    participant Repl
    participant Lexer
    participant Parser
    participant Builtins
    participant Executor
    participant Jobs as Jobs (Vec~Job~)
    participant OS

    %% ── Startup ────────────────────────────────────────────────
    Note over Main,OS: Startup
    Main->>Shell: Shell::new()
    activate Shell
    Shell->>OS: [TODO] install SIGCHLD handler (sigaction)
    Shell->>OS: [TODO] install SIGINT / SIGTTOU / SIGTTIN handlers
    Shell->>Repl: Repl::new(history_path, label)
    activate Repl
    Repl-->>Shell: Ok(Repl)

    %% ── REPL Loop ───────────────────────────────────────────────
    loop REPL loop  [Shell::run() — TODO]
        Shell->>Shell: [TODO] reap_jobs() — drain SIGCHLD flag
        Shell->>Repl: read_line()
        Repl->>User: print prompt (label)
        User-->>Repl: keystroke / line
        Repl-->>Shell: ReadResult

        alt ReadResult::Eof
            Shell->>Repl: save_history()
            Repl-->>Shell: Ok(())
            Shell-->>Main: exit code
        else ReadResult::Interrupted  (Ctrl-C)
            Note over Shell: print newline, continue loop
        else ReadResult::Line(input)

            %% ── Lex ──────────────────────────────────────────────
            Shell->>Lexer: Lexer::new(input).tokenize()
            activate Lexer
            Note over Lexer: skip whitespace<br/>match |  &  ;  <  >  >><br/>handle 'quoted' / "quoted"<br/>fall through to read_word()
            Lexer-->>Shell: Vec~Token~
            deactivate Lexer

            %% ── Parse ────────────────────────────────────────────
            Shell->>Parser: Parser::new(tokens).parse()
            activate Parser
            Note over Parser: strip trailing &amp; → background<br/>split on Pipe tokens<br/>parse_command() per segment<br/>(sets Redirect::Pipe between adjacent cmds)
            Parser-->>Shell: Pipeline { commands, background }
            deactivate Parser

            %% ── Alias expansion ──────────────────────────────────
            Note over Shell: [TODO] expand alias on commands[0].argv[0]

            %% ── Dispatch ─────────────────────────────────────────
            alt single command AND is_builtin(argv[0])  [Shell::eval() — TODO]
                Shell->>Builtins: dispatch(name, args, &mut shell)
                activate Builtins
                Note over Builtins: iterate registered builtins<br/>match on name()<br/>call run(args, shell)
                Builtins-->>Shell: exit_status: i32
                deactivate Builtins
            else external command or pipeline  [Executor::execute() — TODO]
                Shell->>Executor: execute(&mut shell, pipeline)
                activate Executor

                Note over Executor: [TODO] open pipe fds × (n-1)
                Executor->>OS: pipe() × (n-1)
                OS-->>Executor: (read_fd, write_fd) pairs

                loop for each Command in pipeline.commands
                    Executor->>OS: fork()
                    OS-->>Executor: child_pid

                    Note over OS: ── child process ──
                    OS->>OS: setpgid(0, pgid)
                    OS->>OS: dup2(pipe_read, STDIN_FILENO)  if Redirect::Pipe
                    OS->>OS: dup2(pipe_write, STDOUT_FILENO) if Redirect::Pipe
                    OS->>OS: open(file) + dup2  if Redirect::File / Append
                    OS->>OS: execvp(argv[0], argv)
                    Note over OS: ── end child process ──
                end

                Executor->>OS: close all parent-side pipe fds
                Executor->>Jobs: push Job { id, pgid, processes, Running }

                alt pipeline.background == true
                    Note over Executor: return immediately (job runs async)
                    Executor-->>Shell: 0
                else foreground
                    Executor->>OS: tcsetpgrp(tty_fd, pgid)
                    Executor->>Jobs: job.wait()  [blocks on waitpid(WUNTRACED)]
                    Jobs->>OS: waitpid(pid, WUNTRACED) per process
                    OS-->>Jobs: WaitStatus (Exited / Signaled / Stopped)
                    Jobs-->>Executor: final exit_status
                    Executor->>OS: tcsetpgrp(tty_fd, shell_pgid)
                    Executor->>Jobs: update Job.status → Done(code) or Stopped
                    Executor-->>Shell: exit_status
                end

                deactivate Executor
            end

            Shell->>Shell: [TODO] store last_status

        end
    end

    deactivate Repl
    deactivate Shell

    %% ── Async signal path ───────────────────────────────────────
    Note over OS,Shell: Async — any time  [TODO: not yet wired]
    OS-->>Shell: SIGCHLD
    Shell->>Shell: set atomic sigchld_pending flag  (async-signal-safe)
    Note over Shell: actual reap deferred to next REPL tick via reap_jobs()
